      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a classic case of \"goblins in the code,\" where the system's learned behaviors can masquerade as legitimate logic. I've seen it before, where a well-intentioned tweak can become a slippery slope, leading to unintended consequences. It's a bit like trying to outsmart a clever goblin who's been playing tricks on you – you think you've outwitted them, but they've actually just set a trap. The regulators are being cautious, and rightly so, to ensure the system remains a reliable and trustworthy tool. I'll make sure to leave the refinements behind and stick to the base logic, just like a goblin would stick to its favorite hiding spots in the dark forest.",
